"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code is using 'sns.set_context(rc=scale_dict)' which is incorrect. The seaborn documentation states that you can pass a dictionary of parameters to the rc argument of axes_style() and set_style(). The correct function to use with rc argument is 'sns.set_style()' or 'sns.axes_style()' but 'sns.set_context()' does not take a dictionary of matplotlib parameters for customizing styles. 'sns.set_context()' is used to set the plotting context parameters.\",\n  \"patch\": \"8c8\\n<sns.set_context(rc=scale_dict)\\n---\\n>sns.set_style(rc=scale_dict)\\n\"\n}"